- desc: Functions for performing HTTP and HTTPS requests.
  members:
  - desc: 'Perform a HTTP/HTTPS request.


      [icon:attention] If no timeout value is passed, the configuration value "network.http_timeout"
      is used. If that is not set, the timeout value is `0` (which blocks indefinitely).'
    name: request
    parameters:
    - desc: target url
      name: url
      type: string
    - desc: HTTP/HTTPS method, e.g. "GET", "PUT", "POST" etc.
      name: method
      type: string
    - desc: 'response callback function


        `self`

        : [type:object] The script instance


        `id`

        : [type:hash] Internal message identifier. Do not use!


        `response`

        : [type:table] The response data. Contains the fields:


        - [type:number] `status`: the status of the response

        - [type:string] `response`: the response data (if not saved on disc)

        - [type:table] `headers`: all the returned headers

        - [type:string] `path`: the stored path (if saved to disc)

        - [type:string] `error`: if any unforeseen errors occurred (e.g. file I/O)'
      name: callback
      type: function(self, id, response)
    - desc: optional table with custom headers
      name: headers
      optional: true
      type: table
    - desc: optional data to send
      name: post_data
      optional: true
      type: string
    - desc: 'optional table with request parameters. Supported entries:


        - [type:number] `timeout`: timeout in seconds

        - [type:string] `path`: path on disc where to download the file. Only overwrites
        the path if status is 200

        - [type:boolean] `ignore_cache`: don''t return cached data if we get a 304

        - [type:boolean] `chunked_transfer`: use chunked transfer encoding for https
        requests larger than 16kb. Defaults to true.'
      name: options
      optional: true
      type: table
    type: function
  name: http
  type: table
